---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Fast Web Guru"
  description="Fast Web Guru terms and conditions — payment, cancellation, IP ownership, privacy, and service delivery."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-dark py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-white mb-6">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xl leading-relaxed">We believe in being straightforward. These terms exist to be clear about how we work — not to hide anything.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Terms content -->
  <section class="section-light section-pad">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <div class="space-y-10">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">1. Payment Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">Plans are billed monthly or annually via autopayment. Invoices are issued 14 days before the due date. Your plan begins on the date of first payment. If a payment fails, we'll notify you and allow a 7-day grace period before service is affected.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">2. Minimum Term</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Monthly plans:</strong> No minimum commitment. Cancel any month and your plan ends at the close of the current billing period.</p>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed"><strong>Annual plans:</strong> 12-month commitment. No refund if cancelled before the annual term is complete. You retain access to the service until the end of the paid period.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">3. Suspension & Termination</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">We provide a 15-day grace period before suspending service for non-payment. On termination of service, all website files, domain credentials, and login details are returned to the client in full. We do not hold files or access hostage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">4. Ownership</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">Your website, your domain, all logins — they're yours from day one. Full stop. Fast Web Guru does not claim ownership of any client content, website files, or domain names. If you leave, you take everything with you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">5. Client Modifications</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">Post-launch modifications made directly by the client to their website files are the client's responsibility. We're happy to help fix anything — that's what your support hours are for. Significant redesigns or structural changes to the site are quoted separately.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">6. Privacy & Confidentiality</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">All client data, content, and business information is treated with strict confidentiality. We do not share client information with third parties except as required to deliver the agreed services (e.g., hosting infrastructure providers). See our Privacy Policy for full details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">7. Hosting Infrastructure</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">We use reputable third-party hosting infrastructure providers. Our triple-redundant backup system minimises disruption and maximises uptime. Fast Web Guru is not liable for infrastructure events beyond our reasonable control, but we commit to responding promptly and transparently when issues arise.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-t border-brand-border pt-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-dark mb-4">8. Support Scope</h2>
          <p class="text-brand-text-secondary leading-relaxed">Support responses are provided within the timeframes specified in your plan. We provide an emergency contact for urgent issues outside normal business hours. Support hours included in your plan are for website-related tasks; hours do not roll over month-to-month on monthly plans (annual plans may access their full year's hours immediately).</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="callout-box mt-12">
        <p class="font-medium text-brand-dark mb-1">Internal note</p>
        <p class="text-brand-text-secondary text-sm">These terms require legal review before publication. [Internal: pending sign-off]</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
